  <description><![CDATA[<ul>
<li>Great snow coverage</li>
<li>11 lifts and 24 slopes </li>
<li>Over 40 kilometres of piste</li>
</ul>
<p>Voss is one of the largest ski resorts in Western Norway and is located just 100 kilometres from Bergen. Voss is loved for its lively local culture, cozy lodges, delicious Norwegian food, and fun après-ski scene. The breathtaking mountain views and nearby fjords make it a fantastic destination for outdoor enthusiasts all year round.</p>
<h2>Skiing in Voss</h2>
<p>Voss is known to have Norway's best skiing terrain with 40 kilometers of groomed alpine trails and 24 varied descents, including an international giant slalom course and a SuperG course. The ski area offers a fantastic range of terrain for both beginners and advanced skiers and boarders. Intermediates however have the best span available to them, with lots of slopes to master and improve their skills. There are also a range of manageable powder slopes that are perfect for learning basic off-piste skiing. </p>
<p>Boarders aren't forgotten about here, with a big jump, half pipe and boardercross easily accessible in the resorts snow park. The powder fields here are also excellent for freeriding.</p>
<p>Due to the shorter day light hours, night skiing is easily available in Voss. Evening skiing takes place every Tuesday, Thursday and Friday with more than 10 kilometres of floodlit trails for all levels.</p>
<h2>Where to stay in Voss</h2>
<p>We have a handful of hotels in Voss that tick all the boxes for the perfect ski holiday. The <a data-udi="umb://document/2f07f65af1db47f8b2f82ee14b01bf86" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2f07f65af1db47f8b2f82ee14b01bf86}" title="Fleischers Hotel" data-anchor="#">Fleischers Hotel</a> is full of charm and character, having been built in 1864. Located just next to the train station and close to the Voss Gondola station, it is a great base for skiing and adventures. The hotel also offers some fantastic spa facilities for you to use and you'll receive a half board basis so breakfast and dinner will be included in your stay. </p>
<h2>Bars and restaurants in Voss</h2>
<p>If you are looking for a bite to eat, there is no shortage of cafes, bars and restaurants in Voss. Many restaurants in Voss celebrate Norwegian culinary traditions. Expect to find places serving dishes like venison, salmon, and local cheeses. The town's bar scene is characterised by cosy pubs that often feature locally brewed beers. Many bars also offer a great après-ski experience.</p>
<h2>Whats included on an Inghams holiday to Voss?</h2>
<p>On an Ingham's Ski holiday you'll have your flights, transfers and accommodation included. All you'll need to do is decide which activities you want to add on - optional add ons include equipment hire, lift pass and tuition, please see the 'Ski extras' tab below for more information. <em>Our Destination Experts are on hand to help you make the most of your ski holiday</em> - if you need any advice, tips or assistance while you're away, they will be there to help.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>You may also like:</strong></span></p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/336a323374f046cfa0591948e538170e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/336a323374f046cfa0591948e538170e}" title="Norway" data-anchor="#">Discover Norway ski holidays </a></p>]]></description>
