  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<h3>Beginner skiing and snowboarding in Voss</h3>
<p>Voss is a great place for complete beginners, with a free area serviced by a magic carpet in Bavallen, and good progression opportunities on the higher slopes. </p>
<p>Once you have got the hang of things, make your way up the Voss Gondoal and enjoy the wide and gentle green runs back down to the Bavallen area down from Hangurstoppen area. </p>
<p>There are three areas dedicated to children. These include Grebbesbakken, Badnakrokje and Trollbakken. Skiing in Grebbesbakken and Trollbakken is free.</p>
<h3>Intermediate skiing and snowboarding in Voss</h3>
<p>Intermediate skiers can make the most of the 40km of slopes in the area. There is a range of easier green and blue slopes at the top of the Voss Gondola so you can warm your legs up before venturing off onto the more challenging red and black slopes. There are a range of easy powder trails too, so you can test the waters and learn the basics of off-piste skiing.</p>
<h3>Advanced skiing and snowboarding in Voss</h3>
<p>Voss is known for its great snow conditions, so you can expect plenty of powder throughout the winter season. The off-piste is fantastic, with areas just off the side of the slopes and larger back country areas for you to explore. We recommend hiring a guide to show you the best spots. </p>
<h3>Cross country skiing in Voss </h3>
<p>Cross country skiing is extremely popular in Norway, and Voss offers over 18 kilometres of marked trails. The tracks are available for all abilities and venture round the picturesque village and lake.</p>]]></generalInformation>
