  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<h2>Things to do in Voss</h2>
<h3>Restaurants, food and drink </h3>
<p>Voss is famous across Norway for its traditional dishes, like smalahove (smoked sheep's head) and vossakorv (smoked sausage). In the past, farmers in Voss would smoke their meats to make them last longer, and this preservation method has stuck around and remains a key part of the local food culture. Today, smoked meat still takes centre stage in many of Voss’s meals, keeping the town’s rich culinary traditions alive and well.</p>
<p>You'll find plenty of authentic Norwegian cuisine at many of the resort's restaurants/cafés. The Station Café at the <a data-udi="umb://document/4055523ee9f94f57aeb0ffc0f3213462" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4055523ee9f94f57aeb0ffc0f3213462}" title="Park Hotel" data-anchor="#">Park Hotel</a> and the Ringheim Café are local favourites, known for their delicious dishes. For a truly special experience, the restaurant at the charming <a data-udi="umb://document/2f07f65af1db47f8b2f82ee14b01bf86" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2f07f65af1db47f8b2f82ee14b01bf86}" title="Fleischers Hotel" data-anchor="#">Fleischers Hotel</a> is often considered the best in town, offering a cosy atmosphere and top-notch traditional fare.</p>
<h3>Après, bars, clubs and nightlife </h3>
<p>Whilst in Voss, there are definitely opportunities to go out for a drink or too. Popular venues include the Top Spot at <a data-udi="umb://document/2f07f65af1db47f8b2f82ee14b01bf86" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2f07f65af1db47f8b2f82ee14b01bf86}" title="Fleischers Hotel" data-anchor="#">Fleischers Hotel</a>, the Night Club in the Jarl Hotel and the Pentagon at the <a data-udi="umb://document/4055523ee9f94f57aeb0ffc0f3213462" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4055523ee9f94f57aeb0ffc0f3213462}" title="Park Hotel" data-anchor="#">Hotel Park</a>.</p>
<p>The traditional local après drink is a glass of hot Gløgg - a Norwegian Mulled Wine made with red wine, spices and fruit.</p>
<p>For those of you who enjoy a good pint of beer, Voss is the resort for you. Voss is known around the world for it's beer brewing traditions, using a unique yeast to achieve that delicious taste. You'll have the opportunity to book and join a tasting experience in resort in one of the many breweries, or visit the Eldhuset Dale to see the traditional brewing methods in action.</p>
<h3>Shopping</h3>
<p>If you are looking to do a bit of shopping, head over to the centre of Voss (Vagen) where you'll find a range of shops selling sports equipment and the latest ski gear, clothing stores, art and souvenirs.  Outside of the town centre, the Amfi Voss shopping centre has a great range of homeware stores, clothing shops and a supermarket, as well as a handful of restaurants.</p>
<h3>Spas and relaxation </h3>
<p>For a moment of peace, the Voss Active outdoor spa is a wonderful place to unwind. There are three Jacuzzis and a wood-fired sauna, both overlooking the lake and nearby mountains. It is a lovely place to rejuvenate after a day of arctic adventures. </p>
<p>If you are staying at the <a data-udi="umb://document/2f07f65af1db47f8b2f82ee14b01bf86" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2f07f65af1db47f8b2f82ee14b01bf86}" title="Fleischers Hotel" data-anchor="#">Fleischers Hotel</a>, there is a lovely wellness area with an indoor pool and jacuzzi available for hotel residents. </p>
<h3>Culture, arts and events in Voss</h3>
<p>If you want to learn a bit more about what life was like centuries ago in Voss, the Voss Folke Museum allows you to get a unique insight into the building traditions and lives of the past. It’s set in a beautiful location across several historic buildings that you can wander around at your leisure.</p>
<h2>Voss Resort Activities </h2>
<h3>Voss Gondola</h3>
<p>Head up the Voss gondola and enjoy panoramic views of the mountains surrounding the resort.  It is the starting point for many of the ski routes, however if you don't ski and are meeting friends and family for lunch then the Hangurstoppen restaurant at the top is a great meeting place. </p>
<h3>Indoor skydiving </h3>
<p>Take to the (indoor) skies at Voss Vind, an indoor wind tunnel. Even if you have no prior flying experience it is a fun experience for the whole family. </p>
<h3>Swimming at Vossabadet</h3>
<p>For an afternoon off of the slopes head to the indoor swimming pool. There are three different pools; a 25 metre long excercise pool with swimming lanes, and an obstacle course on the weekends, a dive pool and a third pool heated to 32 degrees. There's also a sauna and waterslide.</p>
<h3>Activity Centre &amp; Bowling</h3>
<p>Entertain the whole family at the Voss Bowling. Challenge your friends and family to a game of bowling, play a game of pool or darts, there's even a variety of board games.  </p>]]></thingsToDo>
